### How to Upload a File:

# Step 1: Get upload URL from API
# POST /api/v1/storage/upload-url
# Response: { uploadUrl, fileKey, publicUrl }

# Step 2: Upload file directly to Supabase Storage
# PUT {uploadUrl}
# Headers:
#   Content-Type: {mimeType}
#   Content-Length: {fileSizeBytes}
# Body: {binary file data}

# Step 3: Save file metadata to database
# POST /api/v1/reports/{reportId}/media
# Body: { fileKey, mediaType, fileUrl: publicUrl }

### Example with curl:

# # Step 1: Get upload URL
# curl -X POST http://localhost:4000/api/v1/storage/upload-url \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{
#     "reportId": "uuid",
#     "mediaType": "photo",
#     "mimeType": "image/jpeg",
#     "fileSizeBytes": 2048000
#   }'

# # Step 2: Upload file (use uploadUrl from response)
# curl -X PUT "UPLOAD_URL_FROM_STEP_1" \
#   -H "Content-Type: image/jpeg" \
#   -H "Content-Length: 2048000" \
#   --data-binary "@photo.jpg"

# # Step 3: Save to database
# curl -X POST http://localhost:4000/api/v1/reports/uuid/media \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{
#     "fileKey": "reports/uuid/photo/1234567890-uuid.jpg",
#     "mediaType": "photo",
#     "fileUrl": "PUBLIC_URL_FROM_STEP_1"
#   }'

### Notes:
# - Upload URLs expire in 5 minutes
# - Client uploads directly to Supabase (not through API)
# - This keeps file uploads off the API server
# - Files are served via Supabase CDN
# - EXIF metadata should be stripped client-side
# - Maximum 4 photos + 1 video per report
